sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Searches for files, folders, web links, and shared files across the users content or across the entire enterprise.

Inputs:

  • Query - Query to perform, query is a logical expression that is very similar to a SQL SELECT statement E.g. value >= :amount.
  • User ID - List of owners User ID, defined as a list of comma separated user IDs Eg. 123422,23532,3241212.
  • Direction - Defines the direction in which search results are ordered.
  • Content Types - Limits the search results to any items that match the search query for a specific part of the file.
  • Scope - Limits the search results to either the files that the user has access to, or to files available to the entire enterprise.

Outputs:

  • Content - Returns List of searched content.
    • ID
    • Type
    • E-Tag
    • Item Status
    • Size
    • Name
    • Shared Link
    • Download URL
    • Access
    • Parent ID
  • Size - Information of the created user in JSON format. Will be populated in case of success.
  • Name - Information of the created user in JSON format. Will be populated in case of success.
  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".

Error Messages:

  • Invalid username or password/token.
  • User with the specified login already exists.
  • Invalid input parameters in request.
  • The credentials associated with the Box Spoke connection does not have enough permission to perform this action.

To use this action, the corresponding Box connection and credential must be created and associated with the Box Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
